Program: The History Hour
Title: Tiananmen Square
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3csypyl
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 3 Jun 2019
A student protester's perspective on the Tiananmen Square massacre, the first social network on the internet, the surprisingly controversial early years of Sesame Street, the overthrow of Emperor Bokassa in the CAR, and the death of India's first prime minister, Jawaharlal Nehru. Picture: Dan Wang speaking in Tiananmen Square (credit: Peter Turnley/Corbis/Getty Images) Show less